\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
<\mathcal{O>} & = & \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}\psi*\hat{\mathcal{O}}\psi dx
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

So for the case where x is the observable, the operator is just x and the
 operation carried out would be 
\begin_inset Formula $x\psi$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{x}\equiv x$
\end_inset

.
 Here however, when dealing with the operator expectation value, the order
 of the integral matters as,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\psi*\hat{\mathcal{O}}\psi\neq\psi\hat{\mathcal{O}}\psi*\neq\hat{\mathcal{O}}\psi\psi*
\]

\end_inset

The operator must be carried out on the original wave-function.
