\end_inset

.
 Operators that have this property, that share simultaneous eigenfunctions,
 do commute,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\left[\hat{A},\hat{B}\right] & = & 0\\
\left(\hat{A}\hat{B}-\hat{B}\hat{A}\right)\psi_{i} & = & \left[\hat{A},\hat{B}\right]\psi_{i}\\
 & = & \hat{A}b_{i}\psi_{i}-\hat{B}a_{i}\psi_{i}\\
 & = & 0
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

since numbers commute.
 This is true for the general function 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi=\sum_{i=1}^{n}C_{i}\psi_{i}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\hat{A},\hat{B}\right]\phi=\sum_{i=1}^{n}C_{i}\left[\hat{A},\hat{B}\right]\psi_{i}=0\Rightarrow\left[\hat{A},\hat{B}\right]=0
\]

\end_inset

Therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}$
\end_inset

