\begin_layout Standard
If the field lines were uniform, the force felt by the north and south poles
 would be equal and opposite and so a torque would exist about the center
 of the bar magnet, but there would exist no linear translation.
 Since the field is non-uniform, the north pole feels a greater force than
 the south pole.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\text{Potential energy}\qquad V & = & -\mu B\\
 & = & g_{l}\mu_{B}m_{l}B
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{z}$
\end_inset

